                <head>157. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At 12:30 p.m. on May 17, Mayor Suhr met with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> for about 5 minutes at the White
                    House. No record of their conversation has been found in Department of State
                    files or at the <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, but
                    in speaking to reporters following the meeting, Suhr stated that he had thanked
                    the President for United States aid to Germany. The Mayor also noted that the
                    policy of Berlin was to look forward to the reunification of Germany. The
                    President had replied that the United States also hoped for reunification. (<hi
                        rend="italic">The New York Times</hi>, May 18, 1955, page 8)</p>
                <p>Suhr was visiting the United States May 16–20 to attend the Conference of Mayors
                    at New York.</p>
            </div>
